Q.4. Draw an analogy between a SQLite database table and a real-world example from an app you use (e.g., an Instagram followers list or a Flipkart order history), describing what the table, rows, and columns would represent.


Ans:-

A SQLite database table can be compared to the Order History section of the Flipkart app. It stores all order details in a well-organized format, making it easy to view and manage customer purchases.

Table → Represents the complete Order History.
Rows → Represent each individual order placed by the customer.
Columns → Represent the information related to each order, such as Order ID, Product Name, Price, Order Date, and Delivery Status.

